&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;COMMUNITY CARDIAC REHABILITATION SPECIALIST NURSE/ SPECIALIST PHYSIOTHERAPIST BAND 5 / BAND 6 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; 24.5 hours per week &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cardiac Rehabilitation Specialist Nurse/ Specialist Physiotherapist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Band 5 or 6 dependent on experience and skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Covering Countywide&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;24.5 hours per week –Permanent Post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity is available for a dynamic individual to work within&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lincolnshire Community Health Services NHS Trusts (LCHS) Cardiac Rehabilitation Service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a reliable, flexible, motivated autonomous practitioner with specific knowledge and experience in cardiovascular disease to provide specialist clinical care using well developed assessment skills to monitor health and symptoms of cardiovascular disease, initiate clinical treatments, provide recovery education and advice, refer appropriately and co-ordinate the patients journey across all parts of the health, social care and voluntary sector systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The adult community services provides holistic person-centred care that enables individuals to increase independence, improve health outcomes and reduce unnecessary admissions to hospital or long term care. This is achieved through timely interventions, rehabilitation, management of long term and limiting conditions and partnership working across the health and social care community. All staff within the service work in collaboration with the patient, their carer and other statutory and voluntary organisations and agencies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must have First level registration NMC/ HCPC registration, Degree level qualification or equivalent experience in cardiac care and either have or be prepared to work towards a non-medical prescriber qualification. You must have excellent interpersonal and communication skills, be highly motivated and positive in your approach to maintain a high quality service to our patient population.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be able to travel across the County to locations not served by public transport.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The base of the post holder will be negotiable dependent on the successful candidate&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 15/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview date: 24/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in developing your career then contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alison Bunn Cardiac Rehabilitation Nurse Specialist &amp; Team Lead- 07771 834710&lt;/p&gt;
